ANALYSIS
This bill establishes certain reporting requirements for the department of health and human
services, hospitals, and other covered entities participating in the 340B Drug Pricing Program. The
bill also directs the department to require claim-level 340B identifiers across fee-for-service and
managed care organization claims and implement exclusion rules to prevent duplicate discounts,
consistentwithGAO/CMSguidance.
